data.label:
2. Receives and verifies that the request is valid (Events module).
3.1. Translates the request to the service to be consulted (Translator module).
3.2. Generates a task in the Scheduler module.
4. When the task has reached the execution date, 
Scheduler notifies the Translator module to listen to the respective service and obtain data.
5. The data is sent to the owner of the request.

data.label:
The vision of DIFTTT is to enable 
an infrastructure for any chain (IBC or non-IBC) 
to listen to real-world events, on any service, 
that trigger on-chain actions.
